# koku-desktop Rebuild Rules

CRITICAL: After making ANY code change, you MUST rebuild before testing. The old binary has old code baked in.

## Rebuild commands by change type

- **Any change, always run BOTH steps:**
  ```
  pkill -f "koku-desktop" 2>/dev/null; sleep 0.5
  ./scripts/build-ui.sh && npx tauri build
  ```
  Then launch the binary.

## Launch sequence

Always kill the old process first, then launch the new binary:

```
pkill -f "koku-desktop" 2>/dev/null; sleep 0.5
./src-tauri/target/release/koku-desktop
```

## Default rebuild command

ALWAYS run `./scripts/build-ui.sh && npx tauri build`. BOTH commands, every time. No exceptions. Do NOT use `cargo build --release` alone or `npx tauri build` alone.

## Common mistakes

1. Editing `proxy.rs` and forgetting to `cargo build --release` — the HTML injection is compiled into the Rust binary, not read at runtime.
2. Running `npx tauri dev` — this project has no frontend dev server. Use `cargo build --release` + run the binary, or `npx tauri build`.
3. Not killing the old process before launching — two instances will conflict.
